cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper proposes a new framework for data augmentation called Data Interpolating Prediction (DIP) and compares it to the commonly used Mixup method. The paper focuses on classification tasks and discusses the generalization error and Rademacher complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) experiments. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and the potential for DIP to improve performance in various applications, which makes cs.AI a likely sub-category as well.
